   {:e #blake3 "d27620551842df464c62feb1adb0da0218d6ea1457704044c39ed277cf961b2c" :a :task/description :v "TESTS for DW0b flush guard. CRITICAL TEST (The Iron Test): (1) test_concurrent_flush_no_data_loss: Create tempdir store. Fork two child processes: Process A writes observe 'alpha' and exits. Process B writes observe 'beta' and exits. Wait for both. Open store.bin. Verify BOTH alpha AND beta observations present. Repeat 20 times to catch race conditions. LOG: For each iteration: PIDs, flush order (which wrote store.bin last — check mtime), known_hashes at flush time, final datom count. UNIT: (2) test_flush_skips_when_unknown_hashes: Open LiveStore (knows 5 hashes). Write 2 .edn files directly to disk. Call flush(). Verify store.bin NOT overwritten (mtime unchanged). Verify dirty flag cleared (silently skipped). (3) test_flush_writes_when_all_known: Open LiveStore (knows 5). Write 1 txn through LiveStore (now knows 6). No external writes. Flush. Verify store.bin updated with 6 datoms. (4) test_flock_serializes_concurrent_flushes: Fork two processes, each opens LiveStore and writes 1 txn. Insert 100ms delay in one. Both try to flush. Verify final store.bin has ALL txns from both (flock serialized the read-check-write). (5) test_has_new_external_txns_removed: grep for 'has_new_external_txns' in live_store.rs. Verify 0 matches (or verify it's marked deprecated with a comment pointing to flush guard). PROPTEST: (6) For n=2..5 concurrent processes each writing m=1..3 txns, final store.bin datom count = genesis + sum(all txn datoms). Run 100 iterations. FAILURE DIAGNOSTIC: On any assertion failure, dump: (a) store.bin datom count, (b) expected datom count from .edn files, (c) which .edn hashes are in known_hashes vs disk, (d) flock timing log." :op :assert}
